        DB::table('posts')->insert([
            [
              'id' => '1',
              'user_id' => '3',
              'post_type_id' => '1',
              'title' => 'Virus threat and Indian cotton export targets',
              'descr' => '<p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">The outbreak of coronavirus, which spread from China to over a dozen countries, is likely to pose a major threat to the overall apparel supply chain. However, the Cotton Association of India (CAI), the apex trade body, said that it will not create any threat to India&rsquo;s cotton exports as India&rsquo;s rates are competitive in the international market and the exports can be diverted from China to other markets.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">The apex trade body said there are no specific concerns. &ldquo;On the export front, we are doing good and there is no concern over China virus scare. Exports are going on smoothly and we have so far exported about 600,000 bales (each of 170 kg) to China. Total exports stand at about 22 lakh bales, which means we will be able to achieve our export target very comfortably,&rdquo; said Atul Ganatra, President, CAI, told BusinessLine.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">The CAI in its latest estimate has projected exports for the season (October 2019 to September 2020) at 42 lakh bales. One of India&rsquo;s largest cotton exporters, Kotak Commodities, has indicated that even if China remains a concern area, there would not be much impact on India&rsquo;s cotton exports.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Vinay Kotak, Director, Kotak Commodities, said, &ldquo;There is some concern on the China virus. But if this virus problem is resolved within 10-15 days, then there will be no issue. However, even if the China concerns remain, we may be able to achieve our export targets. Currently, Indian cotton is cheapest in the world so we may be able to gain some extra share in our other existing markets.&rdquo;</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">The existing markets include Bangladesh, Vietnam, Indonesia and Taiwan.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">The cotton rates in India is currently hovering at around ₹39,500-40,000 per candy (each of 356 kg of ginned cotton), whereas the international rates are quoting around ₹46,000, which clearly indicates an advantage for Indian cotton in the global markets.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&ldquo;Our rates are cheapest in the world and we believe that the bottom rate appears to be at ₹39,000,&rdquo; said Ganatra, hinting that India&rsquo;s cotton will have no difficulty finding a market elsewhere.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&ldquo;The Indian prices are tagged with ICE Futures rates (New York market). So, if the ICE futures go down, there will be some impact on Indian prices but that doesn&rsquo;t seem to be happening any time in the near future,&rdquo; Kotak added.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Meanwhile, looking at the India&rsquo;s cheaper rates and the projected cotton output of 354.5 lakh bales for the season, the government cotton body, Cotton Corporation of India (CCI) has conducted procurement of the fibre crop from farmers at the minimum support price (MSP) rates, which is ₹5,550 per quintal.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">The CCI has already bought about 45-50 percent of the overall arrivals across the markets in India. As per trade data, so far about 180 lakh bales have arrived in the markets as of January-end, and the CCI purchased about 48 lakh bales so far. This means farmers are still holding about 50 per cent of the crop.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&ldquo;Considering the current price trend and the stocks available with the farmers, CI purchases may touch about 80 to 90 lakh bales easily during the current season,&rdquo; Ganatra said.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">However, raw cotton prices have remained under pressure as the arrivals peak. The prices at cotton markets across the country were quoted in the range of ₹4,800-5,200 per quintal, which is much below the MSP.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">However, the demand outlook remains strong and trade sources do not see prices to have bottomed out.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&ldquo;There is a revival in the domestic market. So we are not totally dependent on the international market,&rdquo; Kotak added.',
              'status' => '10',
              'is_article' => '1'
            ],

            [
              'id' => '2',
              'user_id' => '3',
              'post_type_id' => '1',
              'title' => 'Weakening apparel export causes to lower cotton import in BD',
              'descr' => '<p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">January forecast of 2019-20 shows less production of cotton and beginning stocks. It seems that the forecast is unchanged as cotton production is lowered again for India, Pakistan, Australia, and Turkey. Consumption is largely unchanged in Bangladesh and Vietnam, according to the United States Department of Agriculture.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
                <a href="https://www.textiletoday.com.bd/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/central-asia.png" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: transparent; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(63, 81, 181);"><img src="https://www.textiletoday.com.bd/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/central-asia.png" alt="" width="619" height="350" style="box-sizing: inherit; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; background: transparent; height: auto; max-width: 100%; clear: both;" class="fr-fic fr-dib"></a></p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">For few months Bangladesh has been seeing negative growth from apparel exports and the weakening apparel exports triggered lower import of cotton in Bangladesh. Many Bangladeshi manufacturers have started to concentrate on producing garments using man-made fiber. Experts opined that the trend will continue, so that the cotton import may be decreased a little bit.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">However, Central Asia cotton consumption is expanding significantly as countries implement political measures to curb exports and to support value-added use. Share of world exports has dropped per annum since 2015/16 as 2019/20 shipments are projected to be less than half of the region&rsquo;s exports just 4 years earlier.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">With stable production, major producing countries such as Uzbekistan, Turkmenistan, and Tajikistan have sought to secure greater domestic supplies for inward processing and downstream exports (e.g. cotton yarn, fabric, and garments).</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
                <a href="https://www.textiletoday.com.bd/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/importers.png" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: transparent; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(63, 81, 181);"><img src="https://www.textiletoday.com.bd/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/importers.png" alt="" width="575" height="338" style="box-sizing: inherit; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; background: transparent; height: auto; max-width: 100%; clear: both;" class="fr-fic fr-dib"></a></p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Uzbekistan banned exports starting this month, a similar measure to Turkmenistan banning exports in 2018/19 (for a brief period); Tajikistan had also discussed following the same measure.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Uzbekistan comprises the bulk of production and use, with the 2019/20 forecast accounting for more than three-fourths of the region&rsquo;s total consumption. &nbsp;Government funding and support for cotton &ldquo;clusters&rdquo; has encouraged foreign and domestic companies to implement a more fully integrated supply chain.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">These companies are expected to improve efficiency of lint production via drip irrigation and machine harvesters (versus handpicked), expand spinning mills&rsquo; operating capacity, and further develop fabric and garment manufacturing as they shift to exports of value-added cotton products versus unprocessed lint. &nbsp;Expanded capacity is evident with record first quarter (Aug &ndash; Oct) cotton yarn exports for the respective period. &nbsp;
                <a href="https://www.textiletoday.com.bd/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/exporters-1.png" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: transparent; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(63, 81, 181);"><img src="https://www.textiletoday.com.bd/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/exporters-1.png" alt="" width="593" height="278" style="box-sizing: inherit; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; background: transparent; height: auto; max-width: 100%; clear: both;" class="fr-fic fr-dib"></a></p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Greater government and foreign investment have also been evident in Tajikistan, as the government proposed to establish a full cycle of processing cotton by 2025. The country has recently expanded spinning capacity with additional government and Chinese investment.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Turkmenistan, the region&rsquo;s second-largest producer, temporarily embargoed exports in 2018/19 (record low volume) to ensure adequate supplies for domestic consumers.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Challenges in regard to expanding exports of processed products include consistent and sufficient domestic crops, affordable electricity, reliable and timely transportation for exports, and mill access to financing.</p>
              ',
              'status' => '10',
              'is_article' => '1'
            ],

            [
              'id' => '3',
              'user_id' => '3',
              'post_type_id' => '1',
              'title' => 'Knitwear exports post slight gain in 2019',
              'descr' => '<p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Amid negative growth in woven products export earnings, Bangladesh&rsquo;s export shipment of knitwear goods posted a 1.20% growth to $16.44 billion in the last year.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Talking to Textile Today, trade analysts and sector people&nbsp;have given credit to&nbsp;the strong backward linkage industry of the knitwear sector&nbsp;for the growth.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
                <a href="https://www.textiletoday.com.bd/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Bangladesh-Knitwear-exports-2019.jpg" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: transparent; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(63, 81, 181);"><img src="https://www.textiletoday.com.bd/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Bangladesh-Knitwear-exports-2019.jpg" alt="Bangladesh Knitwear exports 2019" width="621" height="385" sizes="(max-width: 621px) 100vw, 621px" style="box-sizing: inherit; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; background: transparent; height: auto; max-width: 100%; clear: both;" class="fr-fic fr-dib"></a></p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">According to the Export Promotion Bureau&nbsp;(EPB)&nbsp;data,&nbsp;Bangladesh earned $16.44 billion from knitwear export in 2019, which was $16.24 billion in the previous year.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">On the other&nbsp;hand, export earnings from woven products declined by 0.30% to $16.63 billion, which was $16.68 billion in the previous year.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">However, in the last year, overall export earnings from the apparel sector saw a 0.44% decline to $33.07 billion.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&ldquo;Bangladesh has a very strong backward linkage industry for knitwear goods. About 85% of demands of fabrics can be met by local manufacturers,&rdquo; Bangladesh Knitwear Manufacturers and Exporters Association (BKMEA) first Vice President Mohammad Hatem told Textile Today.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">These manufacturers offer quality fabrics at a reasonable price, which is an advantage for the sector in remaining competitive in the global markets, said the business leader.</p>
                <a href="https://www.textiletoday.com.bd/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Strongpoints-of-Bangladesh-knitwear-industry.jpg" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: transparent; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(63, 81, 181);"><img src="https://www.textiletoday.com.bd/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Strongpoints-of-Bangladesh-knitwear-industry.jpg" alt="Strong-points of Bangladesh knitwear industry" width="640" height="331" style="box-sizing: inherit; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; background: transparent; height: auto; max-width: 100%;" class="fr-fil fr-dib"></a>
              </figure>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">On the other hand, due to a strong local supply chain, manufacturers can ship goods within shorter lead times, he added.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">As a result,&nbsp;global apparel retailers and brands are buying goods from Bangladesh, which helped the sector to remain in positive territory, said Hatem.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Currently, local manufacturers are capable of supplying 85% of yarn and fabric, along with 40% of woven fabric, required by the knitwear sector.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">As per BTMA, there are 430 yarn manufacturing mills, 802 textile mills, and 244 dyeing-printing finishing mills in Bangladesh, along with 32 denim fabric manufacturing mills and 22 home textile manufacturing mills.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-weight: 700;">&ldquo;</strong>The backward linkage is an advantage for Bangladesh, which can help the country to increase the export earnings further even double-digit growth could be restored,&rdquo; Khondokar Golam Moazzem, Research Director of Centre for Policy Dialogue (CPD) told Textile Today.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
                <a href="https://www.textiletoday.com.bd/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Steps-boost-BD-Knitwear-exports.jpg" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: transparent; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(63, 81, 181);"><img src="https://www.textiletoday.com.bd/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Steps-boost-BD-Knitwear-exports.jpg" alt="Steps boost BD Knitwear exports" width="640" height="368" style="box-sizing: inherit; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; background: transparent; height: auto; max-width: 100%; clear: both;" class="fr-fic fr-dib"></a></p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">For tapping the opportunity of backward linkage as a tool of fortune,&nbsp;it is high time for manufacturers to concentrate on higher value-added goods as well as fancy items, said the economist.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">On top of that, the sector people have to install the latest technology in improving the product quality as well as automation is needed for the sector, he added.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Meanwhile, another economist also called for proper steps from the government and the exporters to capture the relocation of Chinese business.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&ldquo;Though there was a huge opportunity for Bangladesh to earn from&nbsp;US-China trade war, we cannot grab the share,&rdquo;&nbsp;Mohammad Razzaque, Research Director of the Policy Research Institute&nbsp;told the Textile Today.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Right now, the government should have an assessment of the direction on how manufacturers can gain from the US-China trade war as well as the relocation of investment from China, he said.</p>

              <p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">The analyst also suggested identifying new avenue of goods, which have prospects and are being sourced from China as the buyers are fleeing from the country and looking for new sourcing points.</p>
              ',
              'status' => '10',
              'is_article' => '1'
